<p>Health officials are currently taking steps to prevent the introduction and spread of COVID-19 ("Coronavirus") into communities across the United States. <a href="http://www.coronavirus.gov/">Coronavirus.gov</a> offers the most up to date information about this rapidly evolving situation.</p>
<p>Through collaboration and coordination with State and local health departments, State and local educational agencies, other education officials, and elected officials, schools can disseminate critical information about the disease and its potential transmission to students, families, staff, and community.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus">The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)</a> has provided <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/community/schools-childcare/index.html">guidance for school settings</a>.</p>

  <h3>Additional Resources for Elementary and Secondary Schools:</h3>
