<li>Broad flexibilities provided to states to <a href="https://www2.ed.gov/policy/gen/guid/secletter/200320.html">bypass ESSA mandated testing</a> for the 2019-2020 school year due to COVID-19 national emergency. States education leaders can find the <a href="https://oese.ed.gov/files/2020/03/template-assessmentwaiver-19-20.pdf">waiver application here</a>. (March 20, 2020)</li>
  <li>
<a href="https://www2.ed.gov/about/offices/list/ocr/docs/ocr-coronavirus-fact-sheet.pdf">Fact Sheet: Addressing the Risk of COVID-19 in Schools While Protecting the Civil Rights of Students [<strong>PDF,</strong> 385KB]</a> (<a href="https://www2.ed.gov/about/offices/list/ocr/docs/ocr-coronavirus-fact-sheet-es.pdf">Español</a>)  (March 16, 2020)</li>
